---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — HeartSwept">
  <main class="page-enter max-w-[720px] mx-auto px-8 lg:px-0 py-20 lg:py-28">

    <div class="text-label flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
      <span class="inline-block w-6 h-px bg-vermilion"></span>
      About · について
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-heading mb-8">HeartSwept</h1>

    <div class="w-10 h-[2px] bg-vermilion mb-10"></div>

    <div class="text-body space-y-6">
      <p>
        HeartSwept is a curated literary anthology devoted to the quiet forms — haiku, lyric free verse, and the short story as breath. Each piece is chosen not for what it says, but for the space it leaves behind.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name comes from the Japanese concept of <em class="text-ink-mid not-italic font-medium">心に吹く風</em> — a wind that passes through the heart. These are not dramatic works. They are small weather.
      </p>
      <p>
        We publish seasonally, attending to the rhythms of the natural year as classical Japanese poetry always has: spring's loosening, summer's heat and firefly dusk, autumn's amber stillness, winter's austere clarity.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you have a piece you believe belongs here, we invite you to submit. The only requirement is restraint — and that the work be true.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-10 border-t border-ink/10">
      <a
        href="/anthology"
        class="text-cta inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-vermilion no-underline transition-all duration-200 hover:gap-4"
      >
        Read the Anthology →
      </a>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
